msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator1"
msgstr ""
"Hello there, I suppose you are here to see my finest invention - the De-Fossilator.\n"
" ... No? You're here to investigate why the Greenwash staff went on strike\n"
" and got locked out by the Enforcers?"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator2"
msgstr "While you're here you might as well see the De-Fossilator in action."

msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator3"
msgstr "Ah, I see you have a toothed bird fossil. Shall I de-fossilate it?"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator4"
msgstr "It worked! The fossil turned into a Rhincus!"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator5"
msgstr "Ah, I see you have an ancient dog fossil. Shall I de-fossilate it?"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator6"
msgstr "It worked! The fossil turned into a Shammer!"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator7"
msgstr "Maybe another time then."

msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator8"
msgstr "Ah, I see you have two ancient fossils. Shall I de-fossilate both?"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_fossilisator9"
msgstr "It worked! The fossils turned into a Shammer and a Rhincus!"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_looten1"
msgstr "Prepare to face the power of my fusion tuxemon!"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_looten2"
msgstr ""
"Well, I guess fusion technology isn't quite there yet.\n"
" We've been working on it for years!"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_looten3"
msgstr ""
"Here's the closest we've come -- it's a cute fusion of an ant and an Aardorn.\n"
" Not exactly the ultimate killing machine Omnichannel wanted us to create.\n"
" I mean â€¦ uh! You didn't hear that from me."

msgid "spyder_greenwash_looten4"
msgstr ""
"The funny thing is, because of its fusion DNA, it makes DNA screeners behave"
" all funny."

msgid "spyder_greenwash_moreau1"
msgstr "You shouldn't be here! "

msgid "spyder_greenwash_moreau2"
msgstr "The fusion experiment blew up!"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_dippel1"
msgstr "Maybe we went too far â€¦"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_dippel2"
msgstr "Or not far enough! "

msgid "spyder_greenwash_aissa1"
msgstr "Stay out - Greenwash has this all under control."

msgid "spyder_greenwash_aissa2"
msgstr "We're all going to die!"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_aissa"
msgstr "Aissa"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_dippel"
msgstr "Dippel"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_moreau"
msgstr "Moreau"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_note1"
msgstr ""
"Note from Dempsey\n"
" 'Fusion experiment risks: unstable creatures, environmental damage, human casualties. Must convince Looten to shut down experiment.'"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_pc_message1"
msgstr ""
"E-mail from Selby to Looten\n"
" 'I've been thinking a lot about the De-Fossilator and I have to admit, I'm getting a bit uneasy about the whole thing.'"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_pc_message2"
msgstr ""
"E-mail from Dempsey to Looten\n"
" 'I've been reviewing the latest data from the fusion experiment and I have to say, I'm getting a bit worried.\n"
" The creatures we're creating are not what I expected. They're... unstable.'"

msgid "spyder_greenwash_pc_message3"
msgstr ""
"E-mail from Looten to Greenwash Staff\n"
" As you are all aware, we are on the cusp of a major breakthrough with the fusion experiment.\n"
" I want to assure you that everything is under control and we are making great progress.\n"
" As you know, our previous test did not yield the results we had hoped for.\n"
" We have learned from that experience and are preparing for a new test.\n"
" It will incorporate the knowledge and insights we gained from the previous failure.\n"
" We have made significant adjustments to the experiment's parameters and are confident that this new test will be a success.\n"
" I want to assure you that we are taking all necessary precautions to ensure the safety of our staff and the success of the experiment.\n"
" Please disregard any rumors or concerns you may have heard.\n"
" Keep up the good work, and let's make this next test a success!'"

msgid "spyder_pc_recorded_conversation"
msgstr "Found a recorded conversation on PC. Play back?"

msgid "spyder_fossilator_flashback1"
msgstr ""
"Selby: I've done it! I've created a device that can reverse the "
"fossilization process. It's a breakthrough, a scientific miracle."

msgid "spyder_fossilator_flashback2"
msgstr ""
"Looten: Incredible! This could be a game-changer. Imagine the possibilities. We could bring extinct creatures back to life.\n"
" We could study them, learn from them, and even use them for our own purposes."

msgid "spyder_fossilator_flashback3"
msgstr ""
"Chip: But what about the ethical implications? Should we really be interfering with the natural order of things?\n"
" What if these creatures can't adapt to the modern world?"

msgid "spyder_fossilator_flashback4"
msgstr ""
"Looten: Ethics? We're scientists. Our job is to push the boundaries, to explore the unknown. And besides, this could be a lucrative venture.\n"
" We can charge a premium for de-fossilating rare and valuable creatures."

msgid "spyder_fossilator_flashback5"
msgstr ""
"Selby: I understand your concerns, but I believe this technology could be used for good.\n"
" We could use it to study extinct ecosystems, to learn about climate change, and even to help endangered species."

msgid "spyder_fossilator_flashback6"
msgstr ""
"Looten: That's a noble goal. But for now, let's focus on the potential profits.\n"
" We can charge a premium for de-fossilating rare and valuable creatures. People will pay top dollar to have their own personal dinosaur."

msgid "spyder_fossilator_flashback7"
msgstr "Selby: I just hope we're making the right decision."

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback1"
msgstr ""
"Dempsey: I'm starting to think this whole thing is a bit out of control. The"
" city's in chaos, and people are getting hurt."

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback2"
msgstr ""
"Looten: Out of control? What are you talking about? We're making progress. "
"The fusion experiment is almost ready."

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback3"
msgstr ""
"Dempsey: At what cost? The city's in chaos, and people are getting hurt. And what about the ethics of it all?\n"
" Creating creatures that could potentially harm humans and the environment?"

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback4"
msgstr ""
"Looten: Ethics? In the grand scheme of things, a few casualties are a small price to pay for scientific advancement.\n"
" We're pushing the boundaries of what's possible."

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback5"
msgstr ""
"Dempsey: I don't agree. We're playing God here. We're meddling with nature "
"in ways we don't fully understand."

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback6"
msgstr ""
"Looten: And what's wrong with that? We have the power to create life, to "
"shape the future. We're not just scientists; we're pioneers."

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback7"
msgstr "Dempsey: Pioneers? Or mad scientists? We're crossing a line."

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback8"
msgstr ""
"Looten: You're just a pessimist. You'll see the benefits eventually.\n"
" The creatures we create will revolutionize society."

msgid "spyder_dempsey_flashback9"
msgstr "Dempsey: I hope you're right. But I'm starting to doubt it."

msgid "spyder_leathergym_board"
msgstr "Chad ${{var:chad_points}} vs Brad ${{var:brad_points}}"

msgid "spyder_leathergym_chadine1"
msgstr ""
"Thanks for joining Chad & Brad Fondent Fitness (C&BFF), we are excited to "
"have you on board!"

msgid "spyder_leathergym_chad1"
msgstr "Yes, I can hear the silence."

msgid "spyder_leathergym_brad1"
msgstr "Yes, I can see the dark."

msgid "spyder_leathergym_chadfort1"
msgstr ""
"Did you look at the paper on the wall? Neverending fight between Chad and "
"Brad."

msgid "spyder_leathergym_bradfort1"
msgstr "Yes, I can feel your heart."

msgid "spyder_leathergym_gigachad1"
msgstr "Why are you here? Having a tough time? Don't worry fellow Sigma."

msgid "spyder_leathergym_virgin1"
msgstr ""
"I love knocking on the door, screaming and running away while someone is "
"using the restroom!"

msgid "spyder_leathershaft2_dude"
msgstr ""
"Shaft is is one of the largest mining companies in the region,\n"
"especially those that contribute to the communities."

msgid "spyder_leathershaft2_achievement"
msgstr ""
"Shaft is proud to join the top businesses in this race toward a net-zero economy\n"
"because we believe that climate change is not only one of the greatest risks facing Fondent,\n"
"but also one of the greatest opportunities for sustainable innovation."

msgid "spyder_leathershaft2_pc"
msgstr "Shaft promotional video on TuxTube."

msgid "spyder_leathershaft2_papers"
msgstr ""
"This leaflet from the Shaft aims to gain the trust of the Fondent's people."

msgid "spyder_leathershaft2_skeptic"
msgstr ""
"I don't trust Shaft. My geologist friend joined a team to explore the river basin\n"
"to determine the impact of deforestation and mining on the river and water quality.\n"
"This will mark the first ever evaluation of carbon and mercury production in mining ponds,\n"
"and their subsequent impact on water flowpaths, ever conducted in Fondent."

msgid "spyder_leathershaft1_sign"
msgstr "Journey to the Center of the Earth!"

msgid "spyder_leathershaft1_miner1"
msgstr ""
"It is important to protect indigenous people, land... but we cannot criminalize the miners\n"
"who are looking for a living to survive. What matters is that the miners are protected!"

msgid "spyder_leathershaft1_beryll1"
msgstr ""
"In Fondent alone there are about a dozen locations where illegal or artisan mining is going on\n"
"but Shaft is viewed as evil."

msgid "spyder_leathershaft1_roxby1"
msgstr ""
"Some islands in the archipelago are completely taken over by mining. It is not possible to differentiate\n"
"between an indigenous community and a mining area. There is not even water to drink. Shaft is against!"

msgid "spyder_leathershaft1_rutherford1"
msgstr ""
"Shaft leader is a thinker and doer. She is not a talker. She has met twice with the miners. It shows quality.\n"
"It shows her plans for Fondent. Our leader has been consistent when it comes to climate change."

msgid "spyder_leathershaft1_surat1"
msgstr ""
"To streamline the mining sector, someone started to give certificates to those qualified to mine.\n"
"The entity? Omnichannel! And Shaft is the scapegoat."

msgid "spyder_papermanor_oldman"
msgstr ""
"I have two sons and a niece. The first is a sailor, and last year he went to the Archipelago.\n"
"The second is a Captain and he transports people. My niece is playing outside."

msgid "spyder_candyhouse2_captain"
msgstr ""
"I'm writing a book about my journey to the Archipelago. It is composed of nine volcanic islands.\n"
"About 1,400 km (870 mi) west of Paper Town, about 1,500 km (930 mi) north west of Candy Town."

msgid "spyder_omnichannel_sign"
msgstr "Omnichannel HQ: We Make Headlines"

msgid "spyder_confusedperson"
msgstr "Confused Guy"


# NPC Dialogues for Legend of Bofie Campaign
# Manhattan ##
msgid "test_lamp"
msgstr ""
"Hello stranger!\n"
"My name is Lampy, lord of all lamps.\n"
"Say hello to the trash can."

msgid "test_trash"
msgstr ""
"Did Lord Lampy tell you about me?\n"
"Go away please! I'd like to rest in peace."

msgid "test_tree"
msgstr ""
"It is me! I am tree!\n"
"You are a butt. I breathe your farts."

msgid "professor_dialog"
msgstr ""
"Professor:\n"
"Ah, yes. The very person I've been wanting to meet.\n"
"I've heard that you want to learn about Tuxemon.\n"
"Tuxemon are little animals, some call them monsters, that we befriend and use to battle other Tuxemon.\n"
"I was wondering, I just received three new Tuxemon for research and I would like to give you one.\n"
"Which one would you like?"

msgid "professor_dialog6.1"
msgstr "Professor: An excellent choice! Hydrone is a water Tuxemon."

msgid "professor_dialog6.2"
msgstr "Professor: A superb choice! Rockitten is an earth Tuxemon."

msgid "professor_dialog6.3"
msgstr "Professor: A great choice! Fruitera is a wood Tuxemon."

msgid "professor_dialog7"
msgstr ""
"Professor: I hope to see you around! I'm about to head on a journey, so "
"maybe we'll meet up sometime."

msgid "manhattan_beach_uncle_jeff_opening"
msgstr ""
"Uncle Jeff: \n"
" Having fun in the sand, my dear ${{name}}?\n"
"Oh! We have lost track of time. You are almost late for your first day of Fire Nation elementary school.\n"
"As a gift I will give you your first Tuxemon. You will most certainly need it at school.\n"
"Which one would you like?"

msgid "manhattan_beach_uncle_jeff_hydrone"
msgstr ""
"Uncle Jeff: An interesting choice you have made! Hydrone is a water Tuxemon.\n"
"Though you two might not get along at first, a water Tuxemon will be the perfect balance to your\n"
"flaming tendencies. Water cools every flameo-hotman.\n"
"Now run to class! Hurry!"

msgid "manhattan_beach_uncle_jeff_rockitten"
msgstr ""
"Uncle Jeff: A wise choice! Rockitten is an earth Tuxemon.\n"
"Together, fire and earth complement each other well.\n"
"Fire and earth are indestructible together in shaping our world!\n"
"Good. Now hurry and run to class! You are late, remember!"

msgid "manhattan_beach_uncle_jeff_fruitera"
msgstr ""
"Uncle Jeff: Hmm. Very interesting. Fruitera is an air Tuxemon.\n"
"Air is what breathes life into fire!\n"
"You and Fruitera will be very compatible together.\n"
"Now get to school! We don't want you in trouble on your first day."

# Spin Off Spyder - Eclipse ##
msgid "eclipse_beginning1"
msgstr "I... I still can't believe what happened. Is this really the right path?"

msgid "eclipse_beginning2"
msgstr "Calm Voice: Argon, you've always been one to question everything. But sometimes, there's no right or wrongâ€”only action."

msgid "eclipse_beginning3"
msgstr "Action without purpose is meaningless. Chrome Robo... just a machine, yet... why do I still see its eyes?"

msgid "eclipse_beginning4"
msgstr "Familiar Voice: Argon, you did what you had to. Chrome Robo was a threat. No more, no less. Let it go."

msgid "eclipse_beginning5"
msgstr "Let it go? You make it sound so simple. But it wasn't just bolts and circuits... there was something there, something deeper.\n Am I losing myself? Or have I already?"

msgid "eclipse_beginning6"
msgstr "Reflective Voice: You need to decide what matters to you now. What lies beyond the horizon, Argon? Is it redemption, or ruin?"

msgid "eclipse_beginning7"
msgstr "Cold Voice: Hesitation leads to weakness, weakness leads to failure. Destroying Chrome Robo was only the beginning, Argon.\n You've stepped into a stormâ€”there's no turning back now."

msgid "eclipse_beginning8"
msgstr "No turning back... I'm starting to feel that. But what if the road ahead only brings destruction?"

msgid "eclipse_beginning9"
msgstr "Compassionate Voice: Argon, the road is yours to walk, no matter how jagged it seems.\n You still carry the light of compassionâ€”it will guide you, even if you can't see the way."

msgid "eclipse_beginning10"
msgstr "Can I still hold onto compassion... without losing myself?"

msgid "eclipse_event2_1"
msgstr "Voice of Compassion: You've chosen this path for a reason. Keep moving forward, Argon.\n Don't lose sight of what's right."

msgid "eclipse_event2_2"
msgstr "Voice of Doubt: Every step you take, you leave something behind. Your ideals won't save youâ€”or anyone else."

msgid "eclipse_event2_3"
msgstr "Unknown Voice: You think this road is yours to walk? Your choices aren't as free as you believe, Argon."

msgid "eclipse_event3_1"
msgstr "Voice of Memory: Argon? By the processors, it's really you! It's been a long time.\n Tell meâ€¦ do you still believe in what we once talked about?"

msgid "eclipse_event3_2"
msgstr "I knew it. You always saw the bigger picture, Argon. Stay on that pathâ€¦ the world needs people like you."

msgid "eclipse_event3_3"
msgstr "Oh, Argon. I guess even you couldn't hold on forever. But don't let this destroy who you are."

msgid "eclipse_event4_1"
msgstr "Voice of Challenge: Well, look who it is. Argon, still fighting the good fight, I assume?\n Tell me, have you grown tired of clinging to your ideals yet?"

msgid "eclipse_event4_2"
msgstr "Hmph. Idealism is a fool's comfort, Argon. But maybe you'll prove me wrong. Doubt it, though."

msgid "eclipse_event4_3"
msgstr "Ha! Finally, some clarity. Just remember, Argon, the world doesn't wait for dreamers."

msgid "eclipse_event5_1"
msgstr "TuxeVault... the institution that funded my dreamsâ€”and my nightmares. Am I here for redemption or reckoning?"

msgid "eclipse_event5_2"
msgstr "Voice of Judgment: Redemption and reckoning are illusions, Argon. What you seek is truthâ€”and truth rarely comforts."

msgid "eclipse_event6_1"
msgstr "Whispered Voice: This is where power lies, disguised as virtue. Do you feel safe here, Argon? You shouldn't."

msgid "eclipse_event6_2"
msgstr "Echo of the Past: You stood in labs just like these once. Healing, creating, destroyingâ€¦ Was it worth it?"

msgid "eclipse_event7_1"
msgstr "Voice of Temptation: Drown your regrets here, Argon. It's easier than facing them, isn't it?"

msgid "eclipse_event7_2"
msgstr "Fragment of Memory: We laughed once, in a place like this. Before it all fell apart. Do you remember, Argon?"

msgid "eclipse_event8_1"
msgstr "Voice of Wisdom: You carry heavy burdens, child. But storms pass, and even the tallest trees find the light again."

msgid "eclipse_event8_2"
msgstr "Voice of Warning: The Cathedral casts long shadows. Be wary of what you find here, Argonâ€”it may consume you."

msgid "eclipse_event9_1"
msgstr "Voice of the Vault: You return to the place that built you, Argon. But foundations crack, and dreams rot.\n Will you rebuildâ€”or burn it down?"

msgid "eclipse_event9_2"
msgstr "I said I came for redemptionâ€¦ but maybe I came to see what's left of me here."

msgid "eclipse_event9_3"
msgstr "Voice of Judgment: Redemption and reckoning are illusions, Argon. What you seek is truthâ€”and truth rarely comforts."

msgid "eclipse_event9_4"
msgstr "Voice of Compassion: You carry pain, but also purpose. This place may have broken youâ€”but it can still shape you."

msgid "eclipse_event9_5"
msgstr "Voice of Doubt: You think you've come back stronger. But strength fades. And this place remembers everything."

msgid "eclipse_event9_6"
msgstr "Voice of Temptation: Forget redemption. Forget reckoning. Just walk away, Argon. Let the past bury itself."

msgid "eclipse_event9_7"
msgstr "If truth is all that's left, then I'll face itâ€”no matter how dark it gets. I won't walk away. Not this time.\n If this place remembers everythingâ€¦ then it remembers who I used to be."

